This paper deals with the analysis of social media data, specifically Twitter, to investigate the propagation of rumors. This falls under the category of social media analysis, which is covered by several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it deals with the analysis of social networks and information diffusion. cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is also a possibility as it deals with the analysis of sound and music data, which could be relevant in the context of analyzing audio content on social media. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possibility as it deals with the application of computational methods to social science research. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible categories as they deal with the analysis of text data, which is relevant in the context of analyzing tweets.
